The global hair and skincare brand SheaMoisture is extending support to entrepreneurs of color whose businesses have been significantly affected by the COVID-19 pandemic.
According to Forbes, the company announced the launch of a $1 million relief fund for diverse business owners.
The fund will help small minority-owned businesses that have been dedicated to supporting those in need amid the public health crisis.
“During this unprecedented time of upheaval, small businesses are being disproportionately affected,” Cara Sabin, CEO of Sundial Brands, told the news outlet.
